cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a framework for Incomplete Multi-view Learning (IML) that involves embedding learning and low-rank approximation. This is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision, which suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories. Specifically, the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories since the paper deals with learning and approximation of multi-view data, which is a common problem in these fields. The paper's focus on clustering also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI and cs.CL. Finally, the use of multimedia data in the experiments suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.MM.
